<header class="page-header container">
  <h1>Security &amp; privacy</h1>
  <p class="lead">A short, user-facing summary. Binding details are in the <a href="/privacy-policy/">Privacy Policy</a> and <a href="/security-overview/">security overview</a>.</p>
</header>

<div class="container prose section section--tight">
  <h2>Your account</h2>
  <p>Sign-in is managed with <strong>Firebase Authentication</strong>. You can reduce casual device access with <strong>biometric lock</strong> (Face ID / Touch ID) where enabled in the app.</p>

  <h2>Financial connections</h2>
  <p>Bank connections run through <strong>Plaid Link</strong>. You authenticate with your financial institution in Plaid’s flow; {{ site.name }} does not ask you to type your bank password into our own forms.</p>

  <h2>Data storage</h2>
  <p>Your plan, planning profile, and linked-institution data are stored in <strong>Google Cloud Firestore</strong> under your user account. How we use processors such as Google and Plaid is described in the <a href="/privacy-policy/">Privacy Policy</a>.</p>

  <h2>Transparency</h2>
  <p>We publish a <a href="/privacy-policy/">Privacy Policy</a>, <a href="/terms-of-service/">Terms of Service</a>, and this site so reviewers (including Plaid) and users can understand what the product does.</p>

  <p><a href="/contact/">Contact us →</a></p>
</div>
